featured_reviews.review_id:
A truly magnificent and serene old Shia Masjid that gives the vibes of Santorini, provides an absolute solace to the heart and tranquility to the soul... Lucky are the ones who glorify Allah in this peaceful sanctuary...

There is also another Shia Asthana, (Qile ka Ashurkhana) around this mosque, which is hundreds of years old and by the looks of it, it seems as though it was constructed by the Shia rulers who established the city of Hyderabad or the elites, it has been renovated now by the devout Shias in the local area.
